A '''managing editor''' is a senior member of a publication's management team. The title also applies to the evening televised  on ABC, CBS, NBC and the FOX News Channel. The anchors of these newscasts also work as the managing  of their newscasts.
In the , a managing editor oversees and coordinates the publication's editorial activities. The position is generally the second highest in rank, after the  (also called the "executive editor".)
In the  a managing editor tends to manage budget and staffing issues at a publication, and may have equivalent ranking to a  in the organisation's structure.
Responsibilities vary from publication to publication. {{journalism-stub}}